Class VitamInstrumentedResourceMethodApplicationListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.codahale.metrics.jersey2.InstrumentedResourceMethodApplicationListener
      • fr.gouv.vitam.common.metrics.VitamInstrumentedResourceMethodApplicationListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.glassfish.jersey.server.model.ModelProcessor, org.glassfish.jersey.server.monitoring.ApplicationEventListener

    public final class VitamInstrumentedResourceMethodApplicationListener
extends com.codahale.metrics.jersey2.InstrumentedResourceMethodApplicationListener
    A fork of the InstrumentedResourceMethodApplicationListener

    This class enables the automatic generation of Metrics/Jersey annotations such as : @Timed, @Metered and @ExceptionMetered on any API end-points of the resources inside the application.

    Metric names are automatically generated under the form:

    URI:HTTP_METHOD:METRIC_TYPE

    Example:

    /application/test:GET:Timer

    WARNING This class doesn't support nested Jersey resource

      • onEvent

        public void onEvent(org.glassfish.jersey.server.monitoring.ApplicationEvent event)
        This function is called every time the application registers an event.

        If the event is of type ApplicationEvent.Type.INITIALIZATION_APP_FINISHED the function will parse the different methods of each Resource and automatically create metrics.
